{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[d:Q11383282]]}} This is a '''List of Shikinaisha in Sado Province''' or the list of shrines in [[Sado Province]] which is present in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}
On this page we will also cover the {{ill|Shikigeisha|ja|式外社|1=Shikigeisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikigeisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikigeisha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 延喜式神名帳|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} of [[Sado Province]] which are shrines that are known to have existed at that time due to other historical records, such as the [[Rikkokushi]], but for some reason were excluded from the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}}. We will cover them in a separate list to avoid confusion.== Shikinaisha (式内社) == {| class="wikitable sortable" ! Prov !! Name !! Kana !! Rank |- | 1 || {{ill|Watatsu Shrine|WD=Q172382}} || わたつじんじゃ || Shikinai Shosha |- | 2 || {{ill|Ohomeno shrine|WD=Q135040480}} || オホメノ || |- | 3 || {{ill|Hikitaheno shrine|WD=Q135040483}} || ヒキタヘノ || |- | 4 || {{ill|Mononoheno shrine|WD=Q135040484}} || モノノヘノ || |- | 5 || {{ill|Mikeno shrine|WD=Q135040485}} || ミケノ || |- | 6 || {{ill|Ihimochino shrine|WD=Q135040486}} || イヒモチノ || |- | 7 || {{ill|Woshikino shrine|WD=Q135040487}} || ヲシキノ || |- | 8 || {{ill|Ohohatano shrine|WD=Q135040488}} || オホハタノ || |- | 9 || {{ill|Atsukushihikono shrine|WD=Q135040490}} || アツクシヒコノ || |- | || {{ill|Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}} || || |- | || {{ill|Shikinai Shosha|WD=Q134917287}} || || |}
